    "text": "today's progress, emoji support! it mostly consisted of `text =&gt; new Intl.Segmenter('en').segment(text).map(s =&gt; s.segment)` in a bunch of places, so that offset calculations made sense. I also had to add a hidden `&lt;input/&gt;` onto the page instead of just harvesting `keypress`, because emoji-pickers don't actually send valid keypresses, but they do trigger `oninput` in a focused `&lt;input/&gt;` :tada:",
